  "description": "Warm-season annual fruiting crop (Solanum melongena, 70–90 days to first fruit). Large-fruited Occidental types produce purple, white, or striped berries (200–500 g). Heat-demanding; slow to establish from seed (requires 12–14 week indoor growing period). Prefers warm soil (25–30°C optimal). Self-compatible but benefits from insect pollination. Requires consistent moisture and fertile soil. White Garden variety (white-fruited, 3-inch heirloom) demonstrates diversity.",
